==General Notes==
* Sendai class CL:
** [[Sendai|Sendai&nbsp;Kai 2]] remodel comes with a [[Searchlight]], [[Star Shell]] and [[Type 98 Recon Seaplane (Night Scout)]], all of these are support equipment that will improve your fleet performance during night warfare.
** [[Naka|Naka Kai 2]] has the lowest level requirement for a second remodel (Lv 48) among CL but comes with decent stats which makes her a very good CL for lower level Admirals.
** [[Jintsuu|Jintsuu Kai 2]] boasts the highest night- and daybattle damage of any Light Cruiser, and is only falling short of the Kuma-Class CLT and [[Choukai|Choukai Kai 2]] in Nightbattle.
** Obtaining all three CL of the Sendai class is required to unlock the third fleet through Quest A14.
* Nagara class CL:
** [[Isuzu|Isuzu Kai 2]] boasts the highest ASW stat in-game, is capable of OASW regardless of ASW-Stat and can perform AACI without Anti-Aircraft Fire Directors
** [[Abukuma|Abukuma Kai 2]] is capable of equipping midget submarines to perform Opening Torpedo Attacks, but is not classified CLT for routing purposes. She also comes with a [[Daihatsu-class Landing Craft]] and is capable of equipping the [[Type 2 Ka-Mi Tank]]
** [[Kinu|Kinu Kai 2]] has a "built-in" Daihatsu Landing Craft providing extra income from expeditions and accelerating the progress of Transport-Phases in eventmaps. She comes with a [[Daihatsu-class Landing Craft]] and [[25mm Triple Autocannon Mount (Concentrated Deployment)]], unlocks a quest to aquire the [[Toku Daihatsu-class Landing Craft]] and is capable of equipping the [[Type 2 Ka-Mi Tank]].
** [[Yura|Yura Kai 2]] is capable of equipping midget submarines to perform Opening Torpedo Attacks, but is not classified CLT for routing purposes. She is also capable of equipping '''Seaplane Fighters''' and Seaplane Bombers, [[Daihatsu-class Landing Craft]], [[Type 2 Ka-Mi Tank]], [[Skilled Carrier-based Aircraft Maintenance Personnel|SCAMP]] and can equip the 8cm-Series of High-Angle Guns in a [[Reinforcement Expansion]]. This wide array of tools makes her one of the most versitile Ships in the game. She also comes with the useful [[Type 0 Recon SeaPlane Model 11 B]].
* Kuma class CL:
** [[Tama|Tama Kai 2]] is capable of equipping '''Seaplane Fighters''', Seaplane Bombers, [[Daihatsu-class Landing Craft]], [[Type 2 Ka-Mi Tank]], [[Skilled Carrier-based Aircraft Maintenance Personnel|SCAMP]] and [[Ka-type Observation Autogyro]]s. She comes with [[Arctic camouflage (+ Arctic equipment)]], from which she and [[Kiso]] get bonuses and is capable of equipping Medium Armour in a [[Reinforcement Expansion]].
** [[Kiso|Kiso Kai 2]], [[Kitakami|Kitakami Kai]] and [[Ooi|Ooi Kai]] are '''Torpedo Cruisers (CLT)''' and differ from regular light cruisers:
*** They are no longer considered Light Cruiser (CL) for routing, expedition and combined fleet formation rules.
*** They gain the ability to equip the [[Type A Ko-hyoteki]] and [[Type C Kouhyouteki]] midget submarines, enabling them to perform Opening Torpedo Attacks.
*** They lose the ability to equip Recon Seaplanes and can no longer artillery spot.
*** At their maximum remodel, they are the highest nightbattle performers ingame. Kiso Kai 2 falls short of Kitakami Kai and Ooi Kai in terms of damage, but has better soft stats to boot.
* [[:Category:Agano Class|Agano Class]] Light Cruisers are capable of equipping the 8cm-Series of High-Angle Guns in a [[Reinforcement Expansion]]. They also gain the ability to equip Medium Armour and Seaplane Bombers at Kai.
* Tenryuu class CL:
** [[Tenryuu|Tenryuu Kai 2]] gains the ability to equip [[Ka-type Observation Autogyro]] and [[Type 96 150cm Searchlight]], but loses the ability to equip Recon Seaplanes, Secondary guns and large RADARs. Her low consumption makes her a good pick for expeditions requiring a CL.
** [[Tatsuta|Tatsuta Kai 2]] gains the ability to equip [[Daihatsu-class Landing Craft]], [[Type 2 Ka-Mi Tank]] and [[Ka-type Observation Autogyro]], but loses the ability to equip Recon Seaplanes, Secondary guns and large RADARs. She is capable of performing OASW regardless of her ASW stat. Her low consumption and ability to equip Landing craft make her a excellent pick for expeditions requiring a CL.
* [[Yuubari|Yuubari Kai]], [[Ooyodo|Ooyodo Kai]], [[Gotland|Gotland Kai]], [[Duca degli Abruzzi|Duca degli Abruzzi Kai]] and [[G. Garibaldi|G. Garibaldi Kai]] are the only Light Cruisers with 4 equipment slots.
** [[Gotland|Gotland Kai]] is capable of equipping the [[Type 96 150cm Searchlight]], [[Skilled Carrier-based Aircraft Maintenance Personnel|SCAMP]], Medium Armour, has a special AACI and comes with the rare [[Bofors 40mm Quad Twin Autocannon Mount]]
** [[Ooyodo]] is capable of equipping the 10cm-Series of Carriage High-Angle gun mounts in a [[Reinforcement Expansion]]
* The Training Cruisers [[Katori|Katori Kai]] and [[Kashima|Kashima Kai]] also have four slots, but are unable to fill fleet composition requirements.
** [[:Category:Katori Class|Katori-class]] Training Cruisers give an experience boost to any fleet they are a part of. This boost will be increased if the Training Cruiser is in the flagship position. This stacks between training cruisers, even if one is flagship (e.g.,if you have both [[Katori]] and [[Kashima]] in your fleet, it will get twice the experience bonus, or extra if one is flagship).

